---

## 📚 Room Summary
  This room explained how to access a Linux machine remotely using SSH. Explained more common commands used in the terminal and provied examples and small task to
understand how the commands operate and run. Also had a small introduction to file permissions and switching users.

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts Learned
- Secure Shell (SSH) is the means of connecting and interacting with a remote Linux machine
-Linux terminal commands learned
    - touch creates a new file
    - mkdir creates a new directory
    - file determines the file type
    - Permissions, r,w,e (Read, Write, Execute)
- Common Directories
    - /etc stores system files for operating system
    - /var stores data that is written or accessed by services and applications running on the system
    - /root home for the "root" system user
    - /tmp temparary stores data that needs to be accessed few times, everything is deleted when machine is turned off

---

## 🛠️ Tools / Commands Used
- Access a Linux Machine using SSH

